      "writtenOn": "2021-02-15T09:24:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Currently, resultsHandler has three methods to report test results:\n\n1. results.json (return value of processMessages)\n2. streamed_results.jsonl (r.streamWriter)\n3. Progress gRPC (r.state.reportsClient)\n\nIf we call r.reportResult only when terminatedByRTD\u003dfalse, we\u0027ll introduce inconsistency among these three methods. So we should call reportResult unconditionally.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 597,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 599,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "aa2adf01f711201d2be6123120851e607a335103",
