      "writtenOn": "2021-02-17T18:25:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we may get a terminate message while reporting result during following function in processMessages:\n\n\tdefer func() {\n\t\tfor _, state :\u003d range r.currents {\n\t\t\tstate.result.Errors \u003d append(state.result.Errors, EntityError{time.Now(), testing.Error{Reason: incompleteTestMsg}})\n\t\t\tif state.result.Type \u003d\u003d testing.EntityTest {\n\t\t\t\tr.state.failuresCount++\n\t\t\t\tr.streamWriter.write(\u0026state.result, true)\n\t\t\t\tr.reportResult(ctx, \u0026state.result)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}()\n\nIf we get a terminate in r.reportResult(ctx, \u0026state.result), I don\u0027t see there are better ways for us to return an errUserReqTermination.",
